Rick Florian (born April 10, 1962) is a musician, songwriter and producer, most known for being the lead singer of contemporary Christian music rock band White Heart since 1986.
Florian works as a real estate agent, though he has sung on several music projects over the years.
Florian was born in South Bend, Indiana, in 1962.
He graduated from Taylor University in 1984.
Florian issued a statement several years ago that the band was only at "a dormant stage".
